            . I was going over <placeName id="t17710911-48-crimeloc256">London bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17710911-48-crimeloc256" type="placeName" value="London bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17710911-48-crimeloc256" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17710911-48-off254 t17710911-48-crimeloc256"></join> on the 11th of September about ten in the evening; a gentleman came up to me about the middle of the bridge and asked me if I had not lost my handkerchief; I felt in my pocket and missed it; the gentleman took me back a little way and shewed me Westbrook, and said he had it; I went to him and saw him give my handkerchief to Taylor; they were standing whispering together; I seized them both, and saw Taylor throw it on the ground; I took them to the watch house and gave them in charge of the constable, (the handkerchief produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Westbrook's Defence.</p>
               <p>I am a carman, and work for Mr. Cooper, in Church-lane; I saw the handkerchief on the ground and took it up; Taylor came up to me and asked what I had found; I said a handkerchief; he said it was full of holes, and threw it away.</p>
               <p>Taylor's Defence.</p>
               <p>What Westbrooke has said, is the truth.</p>
